OL,3,CGovernment brings in Bill to remove
OL,4,C'outdated' hereditary peers from Lords
OL,6,FOfficials have previously described
OL,7,Fthe continued presence of hereditary
OL,8,Fpeers in the Lords as "outdated and
OL,9,Findefensible", with reform "long
OL,10,Foverdue and essential".
OL,12,FBut Conservative critics have called
OL,13,Fthe move a "vendetta" and "political
OL,14,Fvandalism".
OL,16,FNick Thomas-Symonds, minister for the
OL,17,Fconstitution, said the legislation was
OL,18,Fa "landmark reform to our
OL,19,Fconstitution".
