OL,3,CGovernment brings in Bill to remove
OL,4,C'outdated' hereditary peers from Lords
OL,6,FThe total also includes two peers, the
OL,7,FEarl Marshal and Lord Great
OL,8,FChamberlain, whose right to sit and
OL,9,Fvote in the House of Lords will be
OL,10,Fremoved, however they will retain the
OL,11,Fconstitutional duties they perform on
OL,12,Fstate occasions.
OL,14,FBaroness Angela Smith, the Leader of
OL,15,Fthe House of Lords, said: "While
OL,16,Frecognising the valuable contributions
OL,17,Fmany hereditary peers have made to
OL,18,FParliament, it is right that this
OL,19,Freform is being brought forward now,
OL,20,Fcompleting work we began 25 years ago.
